This paper observes the Hong Kong Government's position on Internet issues, and discusses why present computerrelated legislation fails to attain its goal of anti-hacking. The paper gives a Hong Kong perspective to government's e ort to curb intrusion of businesses on the Internet. The Internet has grown dramatically in recent years with tens of millions of people having access to it. There are also increases in both varieties and number of businesses operating on the Internet. It is therefore more pro table for serious intruders to break into the global network and obtain illegal access to network resources. The situation will only deteriorate if not handled promptly and in a proper manner.